<br>
Klaian (Druid of the 34th Season) &lt;Veeshan&gt; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ulilwolf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>LilWolf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(7/25/01 3:34:05 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: First Time Quad Kitting</span><hr size=1> First piece of advice... wait until 36+ unless your really twinked.  with 172 wis I was barely able to quad much without running oom.  <br>
<br>
anyway, find some low low blues that are close to each other and wont pick up stragglers, and some room.<br>
<br>
pull quickly to one spot (any super low end dd) and snare when you get there.  grab another same way... ditto... ditto.<br>
<br>
now you have 4 snared mobs somewhat around each other away from others.<br>
<br>
Now run in circles around them until they are all on top of each others (don't really continue to run in circles.  you will want to make a T shape away from them (your at the bottom of the T and each of the others are at the end of the top line.... you will see).  <br>
<br>
Next, nuke. <br>
<br>
If you are lucky enought to get mobs that don't run... then you nuke them all until they are dead.  Otherwise you will get some to run before the rest are dead.  This is when it's nice to have a DD handy. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ulendlfurryfoot.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lendl Furryfoot</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(7/26/01 10:52:01 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Iceclad</span><hr size=1> First I would wait until 35 at least, at 34 between lack of mana and fizzles it is very tough to finish the mobs off.  At 35 with 180 or higher Wis, you can quad Cougars very easily.  Run past the Tower to near the ice bridge headed to where the boat comes in.  Quad in this area being careful to only get 4 cougars, hehe, because they can be trouble!  If u get an extra run along the waters edge and root the extra cougar.  Then just proceed to quad back along the same shore you just ran down.  Just a thought tho, u can quad in several spots, but I feel this is the best spot for 35-39.  It took me 3 and a half hrs to get through 35 with 199 wis :)<br>
<br>
Lendl Furryfoot<br>
39th Druid of the Tribunal <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/unorpin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Norpin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(7/26/01 12:35:28 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> First time</span><hr size=1> One thing you should do is before you try quading, make sure you can kill one of that mob using your quading nuke.  If you can't handle one, then you need to wait a level or up your wis/mana.  If you can kill one, then try it with two at a time, then three, then of course, four.  If you find that you can kill 3 at a time but not 4, then stick with tri-kiting them untill you level or upgrade, you'll still be getting three times the exp. <p><hr>
Norpin Bramblebum<br>
Halfling Druid of the 36th Season<br>
Erollisi Marr Server<br>
